<p><b>What is 10% Happier by Dan Harris about?</b> Brief summary "10% Happier" by Dan Harris is a memoir about a news anchor's journey to mindfulness meditation. It explores how Harris stumbled into meditation, and how it helped him to become happier, less stressed, and more focused.</p>
<p><b>What are some quotes from 10% Happier by Dan Harris?</b> The only thing you can control is how you handle it. There's no point in being unhappy about things you can't change, and no point being unhappy about things you can. Striving is fine, as long as it's tempered by the realization that, in an entropic universe, the final outcome is out of your control.</p>
<p><b>Who is the host of 10% Happier?</b> Ten Percent Happier with Dan Harris Wondery. Dan Harris is a fidgety, skeptical journalist who had a panic attack on live national television, which led him to try something he otherwise never would have considered: meditation.</p>
<p><b>Who is the founder of 10 percent happier?</b> Today, my guest is Dan Harris, the bestselling author of 10% Happier: How I Tamed the Voice in My Head, Reduced Stress Without Losing My Edge, and Found Self-Help That Truly Works.</p>
<p><b>Is 10 Happier a good book?</b> I agree that if you're looking for a step-by-step practical guide to meditation, this is not the book for you. If you're looking to get a bit of info about meditation and how it can help you, I think it's a great book. I also resonated with many of the harmful internal beliefs that Harris had when it came to work.</p>
<p><b>Is 10% Happier free?</b> A daily meditation coach in your pocket It's the best way to grow your meditation practice and become ten percent happier. After your 7-day free trial, membership in Ten Percent Happier costs $8.33/month, billed annually at $99.99.</p>
<p><b>When was 10% Happier written?</b> In 2014, 10% Happier was published - part memoir, part how-to - and turned into a surprise #1 New York Times bestseller. That book led to a 10% Happier podcast (now in the top 5 in the Health category), and a meditation app that teaches fidgety skeptics how to meditate.</p>
<p><b>What is a famous quote about happiness?</b> “Those who are not looking for happiness are the most likely to find it, because those who are searching forget that the surest way to be happy is to seek happiness for others.” ― Martin Luther King Jr.</p>
<p><b>Who said a happy life?</b> Einstein once said, “If you want to live a happy life, tie it to a goal, not to people or things.” Things are fleeting.</p>
